HEADWORD: Gauntry
<hw>Gaun"try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>chantier</ets>, LL.
<ets>cantarium</ets>, fr. L. <ets>canterius</ets> trellis, sort of
frame.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A frame for supporting barrels in a
cellar or elsewhere.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>A scaffolding or frame carrying
a crane or other structure.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

